  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Adventist Development and Relief Agency (ADRA) works to improve the quality of life for people in need all over the world. ADRA invests in the potential of individuals through advocacy, supporting families in need, health promotion, providing food assistance and water initiatives, establishing livelihoods and responding to emergencies.
In Madagascar, ADRA works in the region of Analamango &#x2014; an area severely affected by the El Ni&#xF1;o phenomenon. The organization operates school feeding programs in 46 primary schools for more than 8,000 vulnerable children. The meals are cooked by community volunteers selected by the school administration. ADRA works with the Ministry of Education and the United Nations World Food Programme (WFP) to select the most vulnerable schools in need of school feeding programs.</narrative>
  </description>
